<div class="slide-content" style="position:absolute;z-index:1;width:800px;height:600px;">
	<h1 class="slide-title" style="text-align:center;">What Does "Escaping" Mean?</h1>
	<div class="quote" style="margin-bottom:50px;padding-bottom:5px;border-bottom:thin solid #333;">
		<q style="font-size:1em;line-height:1.2em;margin:0;" cite="http://codex.wordpress.org/Validating_Sanitizing_and_Escaping_User_Data">To escape is to take the data you may already have and help secure it prior to rendering it for the end user.</q>
		<p class="source" style="font-size:.8em;margin:0;padding:0;line-height:.8em;text-align:right;"><a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Validating_Sanitizing_and_Escaping_User_Data">wordpress.org</a></p>
	</div>
	<p>When we, as developers, escape information we are securing data for inclusion into strings or data streams, including XML, HTML, and JavaScript.</p>
</div>